Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. When boiling, add the @linguine{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until starting to become tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Trim and halve the @green beans{150%grams}. Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the garlic with the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}(for the garlic bread). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a #medium baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over the herby garlic oil. Set aside for later.

Once the linguine has cooked for 8 mins, add the green beans to the same pan and cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, grill your garlic bread on the top shelf until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

While everything's cooking, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Once hot, add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water{75%milliliters}(for the sauce). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the linguine and beans are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @fresh pesto{32%grams} and @peas{120%grams}. Cook until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, then squeeze in some lemon juice.

Stir the cooked linguine and green beans into the creamy sauce, then remove from the heat. Add a splash more water if it's a little too thick.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Share your ultimate pesto linguine between your bowls. Crumble over the @goat's cheese{75%grams}(crumbled), then sprinkle on the @walnuts{20%grams} to finish.

Cut the garlic bread diagonally into triangles and serve on the side along with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!